DIGEST
The digest printed below was prepared by House Legislative Services. It constitutes no part
of the legislative instrument. The keyword, one-liner, abstract, and digest do not constitute
part of the law or proof or indicia of legislative intent. [R.S. 1:13(B) and 24:177(E)]
HCR 53 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Schamerhorn
Establishes a study committee to examine oversized vehicle permits issued by political
subdivisions and related impacts, including the economic effects of such permits, all taxes
and fees paid for local highways, and permitting practices in neighboring states. Requires
the study committee meet on a monthly or bi-monthly basis during the moratorium period
to evaluate current permitting processes and their impacts and submit a written report
detailing its findings and recommendations to the speaker of the House of Representatives
and the president of the Senate by Feb. 1, 2027.
Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
The Committee Amendments Proposed by House Committee on Transportation,
Highways and Public Works to the original bill:
1. Add a representative from the office of operations in the Department of
Transportation and Development as a member of the study committee.
2. Remove the requirement that staffing support be provided by the Department of
Transportation and Development's Permit Department in favor of the Department
of Transportation and Development generally.
The House Floor Amendments to the engrossed bill:
1. Add the executive director of the Louisiana Forestry Association or his designee
as a member of the study committee.
2. Add that a copy of the resolution be sent to the executive director of the
Louisiana Forestry Association.
